            <title>[HBASE-4967] connected client thrift sockets should have a server side read timeout</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4967</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If there is no socket read timeout and if the Thrift server is a ThreadPoolServer then server side threads will be used up waiting for dead unresponsive clients.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
